<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h1>Badges</h1>
    <p>Badges are indicators and have no interactivity. They are used to indicate an item's current state. For example, when viewing the droplet management screen in cloud, a badge will indicate whether the droplet is ‘Active’ or ‘Off’.
    By default, badges are grey and outlined. Green badges should show positive status, red badges should show negative status and warnings.<p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <div class="example">
      <span class="Badge">Read</span>
      <span class="Badge">Write</span>
      <span class="Badge Badge--green">Active</span>
      <span class="Badge Badge--red">Requires Attention</span>
    </div>
    <pre>
      <code><%= display_code('
<span class="Badge">Read</span>
<span class="Badge">Write</span>
<span class="Badge Badge--green">Active</span>
<span class="Badge Badge--red">Requires Attention</span>') %></code>
    </pre>
  </div>
</div>
